    "data": {
        "description": {
            "value": "<p>You gain a sixth sense that warns you of danger that might befall the target of the spell. If you choose a creature other than yourself as the target, you create a psychic link through which you can inform the target of danger. This link is a mental effect. Due to the amount of information this spell requires you to process, you can't have more than one foresight spell in effect at a time. Casting foresight again ends the previous foresight. While foresight is in effect, the target gains a +2 status bonus to initiative rolls and isn't @Compendium[pf2e.conditionspf2e.AJh5ex99aV6VTggg]{Flat-Footed} against @Compendium[pf2e.conditionspf2e.VRSef5y1LmL2Hkjf]{Undetected} creatures or when flanked. In addition, you gain the following reaction. </p>\r<p>\n<hr><b>Foresight</b></p>",
